<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-22-1095 </DOCNO><TEXT>A finite difference scheme for the calculation of the unsteady temperaturedistribution in irradiated tubes of a solar central receiver was developed.The computation code is based on the radiation exchange in the visibleand IR wavelength range, and on the energy balances for tube wall, heatcarrier, and ceramic back wall. The front surface temperature of a sodium-codedreceiver was measured by a thermovision device. The measured temperaturesshow good agreement with the calculated values, and were used to determineheat losses and efficiency.</TEXT></DOC>